                <mrow>\frac{1}{r_4} \amp = \frac{3}{4} + 2\sqrt{\frac{3}{16}}</mrow>
                <mrow>\amp = \frac{3}{4} + \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \approx 1.616</mrow>
            </md>
            so <m>r_4 \approx 0.619</m> cm — about <m>\frac{r}{3 + 2\sqrt{3}}</m> for any equal radius <m>r</m>.
